description: Covid-19 vaccinations on the Isle of Man will hopefully start on 21 December, the government says.
title: Isle of Man to get first Covid-19 vaccines 'next week'
title_page: Isle of Man to get first Covid-19 vaccines 'next week' - BBC News
maintext: Mr Quayle said getting the supply chain right before starting was crucial, as the "last thing that we would want is to vaccinate just shy of a thousand people and then find out that due to supply problems, we don't get our next amount of vaccines within the permitted time".
